            "body": "\r\n\r\n\r\nThis request per se is not actionable. What is actionable are the following (at least):\r\n\r\n- builtin \"frecency\" selector for commands, files, etc. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/660\r\n    - primitives (framework) to make it easier for plugins to build this kind of thing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> Neovim advertises itself as being focused on usability,\r\n\r\nYes, but within the constraint of vim. The goal isn't to replicate vscode or helix.",
